MFEprimer

MFEprimer is a stand-alone version of the web service MFEprimer (http://biocompute.bmi.ac.cn/MFEprimer/). See the web site for details.
It runs on Linux/Unix with Python (>=2.5) and NCBI BLAST (>=2.2.18).
The program is under the GNU GPL license. You will find a copy of GPL license in the MFEprimer tar file.


Requirements:

    Python >= 2.5 
    NCBI BLAST >= 2.2.18 
    
Install

Step 1:
    Make sure the version of Python in your machine is >= 2.5. If not, please go to Python office web site (http://www.python.org/) for help.
    Download NCBI BLAST v2.2.18 (ftp://ftp.ncbi.nih.gov/blast/executables/release/2.2.18/blast-2.2.18-ia32-linux.tar.gz).
    Download MFEprimer from http://biocompute.bmi.ac.cn/MFEprimer/download/MFEprimer.tar.bz2.

Step 2:
    untar MFEprimer.tar.bz2 to '$HOME/bin' directory or other directory. For example, on my machine, $HOME is "quwb",
    
    cd /home/quwb/bin/
    tar -jxvf /file/path/MFEprimer.tar.bz2
    
    It will create a directory named "MFEprimer".
    
Step 3:
    untar BLAST program.
    
    tar xvf blast-2.2.18-ia32-linux.tar.gz
    mv blast-2.2.18/bin MFEprimer/
    mv blast-2.2.18/data MFEprimer/
    
    Make sure the MFEprimer directory contains NCBI BLAST "bin" and "data" direcotries.

Step 4:
    You can create a soft link to MFEprimer.py.
    
    sudo ln -s MFEprimer/MFEprimer.py /usr/bin/MFEprimer
    
Step 5:
    Done.
    Please contact us [zhangcg@bmi.ac.cn OR quwubin@gmail.com] if any questions.
